In an open letter written to the Permanent Representatives of Member and Observer States of the United Nations Human Rights Council, the organisations are asking for action against Tanzania at the Human Rights Council's 41st session scheduled for June 21 to July 12.Â 

They say while they do not believe that the situation calls for a resolution, warning signs of a mounting human rights crisis exist. The letter was signed by the Pan-African Human Rights Defenders Network, Amnesty International, and ARTICLE 19 among others. More from Amnesty International researcher for Tanzania, Roland Ebole... --ChannelAfrica--